{
  "$schema": "https://json.schemastore.org/claude-code-settings.json",
  "_description": "Production acceptEdits profile. Auto-accepts file edits within non-denied paths; prompts on bash commands that mutate state. Active development working mode for production-bound code (Racing Stars, Iskra portal, primus-planning). For scratch/MVP work, use the bypass profile instead.",
  "_safety_notes": [
    "Allow list is broad for read/inspect operations (git status, yarn lint, aws describe-*) so AI can act autonomously without friction.",
    "Ask list catches mutations (deps install, AWS write ops, DB migrations, file deletions) — these trigger the CLAUDE.md decision protocol (options + recommendation + reasoning).",
    "Deny list is the safety floor: secret reads, self-modification, irreversible cloud ops, compound bash bypasses. Cannot be overridden mid-session.",
    "Bash(env) is denied to prevent ANTHROPIC_API_KEY and other secrets from leaking into conversation context.",
    "If you need to work on infra/CI/CD intentionally, do it outside Claude Code or use a separate profile.",
    "Compound bash (&&, ;, ||, |, eval, bash -c, command substitution) is denied to prevent allow/ask bypass via chaining."
  ],
